==English==
===Etymology===
From the French ''[[castorrex]],'' from the Latin ''[[castor]],'' (''[[beaver]]'') and ''rex'' (''[[king]]''). Entered Eng. around 1920.
===Noun===
'''rex'''
# An [[animal]] which has a [[genetic]] [[recessive]] [[variation]] that causes the [[guard hairs]] to be very short or fully lacking.

